He races through the dark alleys. [p]
Perhaps it is because he is familiar with the geography here?[p]
The sound of the harsh wind blowing down from the mountains as it [p]
cuts through the eaves of the buildings, hides my footsteps and my presence.[p]
I continued to carefully tail him, making sure not to lose sight of him.[p]
Finally, his small figure opened the door of a certain building and he disappeared inside.[p]
He went into a motel.[p]
But not into one of the guest rooms.[p]
The door he went through, is one, that is off limits to outsiders, and only for use by employees.[p]
I press down on my heart, which feels like it is going to explode.[p]
With my left hand, open the door that Kaufmann just used, and head inside.[p]


